    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-08-25T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-08-25T10:00:00-05:00" n="473"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">674.84A/8–2552: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 473<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Israel (<persName corresp="#p_DMB1"
                            type="from">Davis</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d473fn1">Repeated to Cairo, London, Paris, and
                        Ankara.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tel Aviv</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-08-25T18:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 25, 1952—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>310. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 304.<note n="2" xml:id="d473fn2">
                        <ref target="#d472">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> advises Israel Chargé Paris saw
                    Egyptian Chargé there, gave him msg substantially as reported <gloss
                        target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> and confirmed it in writing as requested
                    by Egyptian.</p>
                <p>Meanwhile <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> spokesman was reported in
                    press this a.m. as saying, altho no dipl steps yet taken re <gloss
                        target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss>s recent peace gesture toward Egypt, he
                    thought such action “likely”. <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> advises
                    public statement unfortunate and inadvertent. Explains spokesman has no
                    knowledge of steps reported <gloss target="#t_reftel1">reftel</gloss> re
                    overtures to Egypt.</p>
                <p>Emb was informed further that <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> mtg has been
                    called for Tues Aug 26 at Egypt’s request re recent patrol clash. While Egypt’s
                    calling such mtg is regarded as hopeful sign, source stated more significant
                    fact is Egyptian senior <gloss target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> delegate has
                    requested private mtg with Israel senior delegate 2 hours before <gloss
                        target="#t_MAC1">MAC</gloss> meets.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DMB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
